docs.abstract: The decision to remove an episode from its service in Saudi Arabia raises questions of whether entertainment giants will fight for values like free expression.
docs.snippet: The decision to remove an episode from its service in Saudi Arabia raises questions of whether entertainment giants will fight for values like free expression.
docs.lead_paragraph: Under Article 6, Paragraph 1 of Saudi Arabia’s Anti-Cyber Crime Law, the following is punishable by up to five years in prison: “Production, preparation, transmission, or storage of material impinging on public order, religious values, public morals, and privacy, through the information network or computers.”

headline.main: Netflix’s Bow to Saudi Censors Comes at a Cost to Free Speech
headline.print_headline: Netflix Bow To Saudis Is Chilling

docs.abstract: A nuclear power facility proposed for a rugged coastline stretch could lift the local economy while expanding Britain’s non-carbon fuel options.
docs.snippet: A nuclear power facility proposed for a rugged coastline stretch could lift the local economy while expanding Britain’s non-carbon fuel options.
docs.lead_paragraph: CEMAES, Wales — Not far from this harbor village of brightly painted houses on Anglesey Island, a huge construction project is underway. Gates and wire fences are up. Archaeologists are sifting through dirt to document stony dwellings dating from 100 B.C. A technical school is welcoming apprentices eager to learn how to maneuver in high-tech control rooms and operate water-cooling systems.

headline.main: For Wales, Nuclear Plant Would Mean New Jobs. For the U.K., It May Mean More.
headline.print_headline: In Wales, a Renewed Fervor for Nuclear

docs.abstract: Market watchers are divided on whether the current slump will be prolonged or a blip, and history doesn’t offer a clear answer. Expect turbulence.
docs.snippet: Market watchers are divided on whether the current slump will be prolonged or a blip, and history doesn’t offer a clear answer. Expect turbulence.
docs.lead_paragraph: A year ago, in the wake of President Trump’s tax cut, euphoric investors pushed the Dow Jones industrial average past 25,000, a record. The Dow had just gained 25 percent in 2017, and the Nasdaq had leapt 28 percent. Volatility was so low that there wasn’t a single day in 2017 when the S&P 500 fluctuated more than 2 percent.

headline.main: This Expert Called the Market Plunge. Here’s What He Sees in 2019.
